The paper deals with the problem of measuring the leakage of a black-box system, which is a common topic in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The authors propose using machine learning methods to estimate the Bayes risk of the system, which falls under the category of statistical learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the limitations of the frequentist approach, which is a common topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and software engineering (cs.SE).
